paragraphs.text: %md # The Dead Letter Queue management The Neo4j Streams Sink module provide a Dead Letter Queue mechanism that if activated re-route all “bad-data” to a configured topic. What we mean for "bad-data"? * De-Serialization errors. I.e. bad formatted JSON: `{id: 1, "name": "Andrea", "surname": "Santurbano"}` * Transient errors while ingesting data into the DB.

msg.data:
The Dead Letter Queue management

The Neo4j Streams Sink module provide a Dead Letter Queue mechanism that if activated re-route all “bad-data” to a configured topic.

What we mean for “bad-data”?

  • De-Serialization errors. I.e. bad formatted JSON: {id: 1, "name": "Andrea", "surname": "Santurbano"}
  • Transient errors while ingesting data into the DB.

paragraphs.text:
%md

Into the Docker Compose file you'll find the following configurations:

```
NEO4J_streams_sink_errors_tolerance: "all"
NEO4J_streams_sink_errors_log_enable: "true"
NEO4J_streams_sink_errors_deadletterqueue_topic_name: "dlqtopic"
NEO4J_streams_sink_errors_deadletterqueue_context_headers_enable: "true"
NEO4J_streams_sink_errors_deadletterqueue_context_headers_prefix: "__streams.errors."
```

# Let's look at the DLQ with Kafkacat

[Kafkacat](https://docs.confluent.io/current/app-development/kafkacat-usage.html) is a command line utility that you can use to test and debug Apache Kafka deployments. You can use kafkacat to produce, consume, and list topic and partition information for Kafka.
Described as “netcat for Kafka”, it is a swiss-army knife of tools for inspecting and creating data in Kafka.

```
docker run --tty \
  --network neo4j-streams-october-2k20 \
  confluentinc/cp-kafkacat \
  kafkacat -b broker:9093 -t dlqtopic -C \
  -f '\nKey (%K bytes): %k
  Value (%S bytes): %s
  Timestamp: %T
  Partition: %p
  Offset: %o
  Headers: %h\n'
```

**N.b** please consider the the network name `neo4j-streams-october-2k20` is related to the directory name of the compose file so if your compose file is inside a directory called `kafa_neo4j` the network change as `kafa_neo4j_default` and the full command become:

```
docker run --tty \
  --network kafa_neo4j_default \
  confluentinc/cp-kafkacat \
  kafkacat -b broker:9093 -t dlqtopic -C \
  -f '\nKey (%K bytes): %k
  Value (%S bytes): %s
  Timestamp: %T
  Partition: %p
  Offset: %o
  Headers: %h\n'
```
